## Notes (for manuscript footnotes)

1) **Cohort (n=38)**: intermediate/difficult cases within the original 52-case seizure-free cohort, restricted to ILAE 1â€“2.
2) **Reference standard**: resection cavity mask.
3) **Vertex-level DSC**: computed on the lesion hemisphere (rows with `lesion_area_cm2>0` in `vertex_level_results.csv`).
4) **Cluster-level criterion**: a cluster is a TP if `boxDSC > 0.22`.
5) **Precision**: TP clusters / all predicted clusters (pooled across subjects).
6) **Sensitivity**: subjects with â‰¥1 TP cluster / all subjects. In this seizure-free cohort (all positive), this equals the subject-level detection rate under the same criterion.
7) **Pinpointing**: at least one predicted cluster has its weighted center-of-mass (COM) within the lesion mask.
8) **Det(PPV-in-maskâ‰¥0.5)**: subject-level endpoint; a subject is detected if â‰¥1 predicted cluster has PPV-in-mask â‰¥ 0.5.
9) **Det(distanceâ‰¤20mm)**: subject-level endpoint; a subject is detected if â‰¥1 predicted cluster has distance-to-lesion â‰¤ 20 mm (MELD Graph criterion).
10) **Recall@0.15**: subject-level endpoint; `lesion_dice_union â‰¥ 0.15`.
11) **Uncertainty**: 95% CIs from subject-level bootstrapping (`n_boot=10000`).
12) **Paired statistics (TrackA (paper fusion; +20) vs MELD (self-trained; unconstrained))**:
   - DSC / cluster counts / FP burden: paired sign-flip randomization test.
